<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Well, we recently upgraded our computers at work. POS Dells from 98 only to get POS Dells from 04. However, these new Dells only have one serial com port. Computers usually have two of these. Normally this isn't a problem as it's only used for legacy applications and hardware. However, we use a specific software database that interfaces with our registers and it requires....drumroll....com port 2. You can't configure it to use com1 and having tried in Device Manager to change com1 to com2, it gives an ACK error. 
<br />

<br />
My bro has told me I either need to get a new PC, keep using the old one or buy an add-on card. Either way, I'm sorta PO'ed at spending that much time trying to troubleshoot crappy software.
<br />

<br />
While I'm not a fan of Dell computers, I do like their LCD monitors. Some of the best ones I've seen.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
